  <ol id="questionList">
    <br/>
    <li id="q1">What percentage of the working population nowadays are women?<list class="answerList"><li><a id="a1">less than 20%</a></li><li><a id="a2">between 21% and 50%</a></li><li><a id="a3">more than 50%</a></li></list><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q2">Nowadays the average female manager's salary is between ...<list class="answerList"><li><a id="a4">&#xA3;25,000&#x2013;&#xA3;29,000.</a></li><li><a id="a5">&#xA3;30,000&#x2013;&#xA3;34,000.</a></li><li><a id="a6">&#xA3;35,000&#x2013;&#xA3;39,000.</a></li></list><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q3">What is the principal reason for women going out to work?<list class="answerList"><li><a id="a7">They do not want to depend on other people for money.</a></li><li><a id="a8">They can no longer depend on husbands to support them.</a></li><li><a id="a9">They find life more expensive.</a></li></list><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q4">Changes in attitudes in the 1960s and '70s meant that more young women ...<list class="answerList"><li><a id="a10">were able to take office jobs.</a></li><li><a id="a11">went into temporary employment.</a></li><li><a id="a12">received a university education.</a></li></list><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q5">Which pie chart shows the proportion of men and women who are expected to start businesses in 2010?<list class="answerList"><li><a id="a13">Chart A</a></li><li><a id="a14">Chart B</a></li><li><a id="a15">Chart C</a></li></list><br/></li>
  </ol>
