<section id="fb1">
  <p align="left">
    <font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">1. Mary says that now women make up just over half of all employees. In other words more than 50%.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb2">
  <p align="left">
    <font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">2. Mary says that the average annual salary for a female manager is &#xA3;32,000. In other words between &#xA3;30,000 and &#xA3;34,000. </font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb3">
  <p align="left">
    <font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">3. Mary says they want to be financially independent which means the same as not wanting to depend on other people for money.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb4">
  <p align="left">
    <font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">4. Mary says that in the late '60s and early '70s girls started going to university. In other words received a university education.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb5">
  <p align="left">
    <font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">5. Mary says women will be responsible for approximately half of all new business start-ups and this is illustrated by the 50/50 split on the pie chart.</font>
  </p>
